<title>UK: UK net consumer credit up 997 mln stg in August.</title>
<headline>UK net consumer credit up 997 mln stg in August.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bank of England released the following seasonally adjusted consumer credit data -</p>
<p>NET LENDING (previously released data in brackets, in MLN STG)</p>
<p>					     AUGUST  JULY	     AUG,95</p>
<p> Total net lending		     2,673   2,611 (2,546)  1,748</p>
<p>  -- Consumer credit		   997     1,053 (1,027)    558</p>
<p>  -- Secured on dwellings	    1,676   1,559 (1,519)  1,190</p>
<p>BREAKDOWN of net consumer lending BY SOURCE -</p>
<p>  -- Banks				 578    863    (835)    148</p>
<p>  -- Building societies		 24     47    (49)	31</p>
<p>  -- Other specialist lenders	407    158    (152)    369</p>
<p>  -- Retailers			    -3     -6    (-5)	10</p>
<p>  -- Insurance companies		-9     -9    (-4)	unch</p>
<p>  -- Credit card			 326    385    (266)     91</p>
<p>CONSUMER CREDIT (seasonally adjusted, in PCT)</p>
<p> Consumer credit mth/mth		1.4    1.5   (0.5)     0.9</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    3 mth annualised   17.1   15.4  (6.2)     12.9</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    6 mth annualised   16.8   16.0  (6.0)     11.9</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;	  &quot;     yr/yr    15.5   14.9  (5.6)     12.5</p>
<p>  Total personal borrowing mth/mth 0.6    0.6   (0.5)     0.4</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    3 mth annualised   6.5    6.3   (6.2)     4.9</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    6 mth annualised   6.3    6.1   (6.0)     5.0</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;	  &quot;     yr/yr    5.9    5.7   (5.6)     5.5</p>
<p>  Secured on dwellings mth/mth     0.4    0.4   (0.4)     0.3</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    3 mth annualised   4.8    4.9   (4.7)     3.6</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;    6 mth annualised   4.6    4.5   (4.4)     4.0</p>
<p>   &quot;	 &quot;     yr/yr		 4.3    4.2   (4.2)     4.5</p>
